name: KPA 500 Notes
info:
KPA 500 for Node-Red

You will need the Dashboard installed

Modify the Serial to and From the KPA500 to match
your serial ports.

You will require a Serial cable from your
hardware running NodeRed to the PC control on the 
KPA500.

More work could be done in the Fault Conditions and
I never wrote any flow to reset a fault condition,
however, you can power cycle the amp to reset it.

The meter reading cycle is something you may want
to play with.  Those settings are in the 'timestamp' 
button. 

There is more to add, but if you get this far, feel
free to expand to more meters.


^AL ALC Threshold
^OS STBY/OP Mode Selection
^AR Atten Fault Release Time 
^PJ Power Adjustment
^BC STBY on Band Change 
^RVM Firmware Version
^BN Band Selection 
^SN Serial Number
^BRP PC Port RS232 Data Rate 
^SP Speaker On/Off
^BRX XCVR Port RS232 Data Rate 
^TM PA Temperature

info:
You can use the power switch on Node Red to turn the KPA500 off. 

To power the amp on you need to send a logic low pulse to pin 8 on the AUX connector of the amp.

Pin 5 of the AUX connector is ground, so common of a relay would go to pin 5 and normally open of the relay to pin 8 Program relay to close for 150 mS then open.

You can use the Power On function node in KPA500 flow to control a relay.

name: Convert to Command
Station Header
format:
<style>
    .md-toolbar-tools{
        font-size:14px;
        height:24px;
    }
    md-toolbar{
        min-height:16px;
    }
    #weather{
        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
        margin-right:5px;
    }
    #clock{
        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    }
    #infobar{
        margin:5px 5px 5px auto;
    }

</style>

<script id="titleScript" type="text/javascript">

theScope=scope;

$(function() {
    if($('.md-toolbar-tools').length != 0){
        init();
    }else setTimeout(init, 500)
});

function init(){
    createInfoBar();
    loadWeather();
    loadClock();
}

(function(scope){
   scope.$watch('msg.payload', function(data){
       if(data != undefined){
          var payload=JSON.parse(data);
          var p = $("#weather")
          if(p != undefined){
            var text = payload.outsideTemp;
            text += "\u00B0F ";
            p.text(text);
          }

       }
   });
})(scope);

function createInfoBar(){
    var toolbar = $('.md-toolbar-tools');
    $('#infobar').remove();
    var div = $('<div id="infobar"/>');
    //div[0].style.margin = '5px 5px 5px auto';
    toolbar.append(div);
}

function loadWeather(){
    var infobar = $('#infobar');
    
    $('#weather').remove();
    var s = $('<span/ id="weather">');
    //s[0].style.marginRight='5px';
    infobar.append(s);
}

function loadClock(){
    
    var infobar = $('#infobar');
    
    $('#clock').remove();
    var s = $('<span/ id="clock">');
    
    infobar.append(s);


    function updateTime() {
       
        console.log('UpdateTime:');
        var d = new Date();
        s.text(d.toLocaleTimeString());
            
    }

    if(document.clockInterval){ 
            clearInterval(document.clockInterval);
            document.clockInterval = null;
    }
        
    document.clockInterval = setInterval(updateTime,1000);
}

$('#K9KLD_Header').hide();
//let hideMe = '{"groups":{"hide":["Header"]}}';
//theScope.send({payload:hideMe});

</script>
